[SALUTATIONS]

00:10:09.976 --> 00:10:11.277
GROUP
Who's that Pokémon?

00:10:17.050 --> 00:10:18.818
It's Squirtle.

00:10:25.024 --> 00:10:27.527
[EXCITED]

00:10:27.527 --> 00:10:30.330
‐ Wow. Energetic.
‐ So that's a Charmander.

00:10:32.532 --> 00:10:35.168
Charmander.
The Lizard Pokémon.

00:10:35.168 --> 00:10:37.470
'When the tip of Charmander's
tail burns brightly'

00:10:37.470 --> 00:10:39.706
'that indicates
it's in good health.'

00:10:39.706 --> 00:10:41.474
[PROUD]

00:10:41.474 --> 00:10:43.643
All three of the Kanto Pokémon

00:10:43.643 --> 00:10:45.879
new Trainers choose from
are here.

00:10:45.879 --> 00:10:48.448
‐ Where's Charmander's Trainer?
‐ Right there! That's him.

00:10:48.448 --> 00:10:49.716
[panting]

00:10:49.716 --> 00:10:53.153
Hey, it's Trevs.

00:10:53.153 --> 00:10:57.257
‐ I made it.
‐ Trevor, you're so late.

00:10:57.257 --> 00:11:00.894
Sorry. You see, Charmander
was at it again on our way here.

00:11:00.894 --> 00:11:03.463
‐ Again?
‐ What do you mean?

00:11:03.463 --> 00:11:05.131
Charmander was at what again?

00:11:05.131 --> 00:11:07.400
Alright. The thing is.. Huh?

00:11:07.400 --> 00:11:08.701
[PANIC]

00:11:10.803 --> 00:11:13.439
[PANIC]

00:11:13.439 --> 00:11:16.109
[WATER GUN ATTACK]
[RELIEVED]

00:11:16.109 --> 00:11:18.711
Well, Charmander's always
ready to battle.

00:11:18.711 --> 00:11:20.513
I'm so sorry
for Charmander's actions

00:11:20.513 --> 00:11:21.981
towards your Pokémon.

00:11:21.981 --> 00:11:23.816
It doesn't matter
where it is.

00:11:23.816 --> 00:11:25.952
Charmander's always
so full of energy.

00:11:25.952 --> 00:11:27.820
It got into a fight
on the way here, right?

00:11:27.820 --> 00:11:29.088
TREVOR
Yep.

00:11:29.088 --> 00:11:31.357
This is Trevor.

00:11:31.357 --> 00:11:34.027
The three of us have been
friends since we were little.

00:11:34.027 --> 00:11:37.597
How are you? I'm really sorry
about all this.

00:11:37.597 --> 00:11:40.033
Huh! It can't be.
You're Serena.

00:11:40.033 --> 00:11:42.302
‐ Huh?
‐ It's Pokévision.

00:11:42.302 --> 00:11:44.404
That video made you famous.

00:11:44.404 --> 00:11:45.872
Shauna kept saying
how there's this

00:11:45.872 --> 00:11:47.941
really pretty girl
on a video.

00:11:47.941 --> 00:11:49.776
She must've showed it to me
a million times.

00:11:49.776 --> 00:11:52.946
Huh? Uh..

00:11:52.946 --> 00:11:56.549
‐ I'm a little embarrassed.
‐ Wow! You're just so cute.

00:11:56.549 --> 00:11:58.251
‐ So cute, so cute..
‐ Don't mind him.

00:11:58.251 --> 00:12:00.153
‐ He's a goofball.
‐ Huh?

00:12:00.153 --> 00:12:02.422
Ah, are you Pikachu?

00:12:02.422 --> 00:12:04.023
[UNSURE]

00:12:05.792 --> 00:12:08.094
Uh..

00:12:08.094 --> 00:12:09.896
I like to take photos
of all the Pokémon I've met.

00:12:15.902 --> 00:12:19.205
My dream is to meet every
Pokémon listed in the Pokédex

00:12:19.205 --> 00:12:21.507
and someday discover
a new Pokémon

00:12:21.507 --> 00:12:23.142
that hasn't even been
listed yet.

00:12:23.142 --> 00:12:24.777
That sounds great.

00:12:24.777 --> 00:12:28.014
This is Ash, Serena,
Bonnie, and Clemont.

00:12:28.014 --> 00:12:30.883
Ash came all the way
from the Kanto region.

00:12:30.883 --> 00:12:33.119
Then that means you've come
across a bunch of Pokémon

00:12:33.119 --> 00:12:35.188
from Kanto
that I haven't ever seen before.

00:12:35.188 --> 00:12:36.956
I'm so jealous.

00:12:36.956 --> 00:12:39.225
So are all of you guys
staying for camp?

00:12:39.225 --> 00:12:41.494
Uh‐huh.
We're part of Team Froakie.

00:12:41.494 --> 00:12:43.963
All four of us
are traveling together.

00:12:43.963 --> 00:12:46.599
Big group.
Must be a lot of fun.

00:12:46.599 --> 00:12:49.102
You guys don't
travel together?

00:12:49.102 --> 00:12:50.236
TIERNO
The three of us got our Pok mon

00:12:50.236 --> 00:12:51.904
from Professor Sycamore

00:12:51.904 --> 00:12:53.640
on the same day,
but went our separate ways

00:12:53.640 --> 00:12:55.475
to pursue our dreams.

00:12:55.475 --> 00:12:57.677
ASH
Oh, I see.

00:12:57.677 --> 00:12:59.145
SHAUNA
But every now and then

00:12:59.145 --> 00:13:00.513
we like to get together
and catch up

00:13:00.513 --> 00:13:03.016
on what everyone's been up to.
[HAPPY]

00:13:03.016 --> 00:13:04.350
So why are you
on a journey, Ash?

00:13:04.350 --> 00:13:05.818
That's easy.

00:13:05.818 --> 00:13:06.853
I started traveling
so I can

00:13:06.853 --> 00:13:08.054
become a Pokémon Master.

00:13:08.054 --> 00:13:10.290
[AGREEMENT]

00:13:10.290 --> 00:13:12.258
'So becoming a Pokémon Master
is your dream, huh?'

00:13:12.258 --> 00:13:13.359
Sure is.

00:13:16.262 --> 00:13:17.630
NURSE JOY
'Alright, it's time to gather

00:13:17.630 --> 00:13:19.332
on the beach for introductions'

00:13:19.332 --> 00:13:21.634
'as the Pokémon summer camp
gets under way.'

00:13:21.634 --> 00:13:23.503
‐ Come on, let's hurry.
‐ Alright.

00:13:23.503 --> 00:13:24.737
Yay!

00:13:24.737 --> 00:13:27.106
[EXCITED]

00:13:27.106 --> 00:13:29.809
Dreams, huh?

00:13:29.809 --> 00:13:31.144
What's wrong, Serena?

00:13:31.144 --> 00:13:35.548
Huh. Nothing. I'm coming.

00:13:35.548 --> 00:13:37.417
PROFESSOR SYCAMORE
Hello, Trainers.

00:13:37.417 --> 00:13:38.985
Thank you all for being here.

00:13:38.985 --> 00:13:40.953
And why are you here?

00:13:40.953 --> 00:13:42.522
You're here to build
an even deeper bond

00:13:42.522 --> 00:13:44.490
'with your Pokémon'

00:13:44.490 --> 00:13:46.592
'through your interactions
with other Trainers.'

00:13:46.592 --> 00:13:48.895
'Starting today
and throughout the week.'

00:13:48.895 --> 00:13:50.229
'I hope you'll have
lots of summer camp fun.'

00:13:51.964 --> 00:13:54.901
And now,
presenting Nurse Joy.

00:13:54.901 --> 00:13:58.638
She's opened a Pokémon Center
just for us.

00:13:58.638 --> 00:14:01.107
I'm happy to care for your
Pokémon anytime you need me.

00:14:01.107 --> 00:14:02.675
[AGREEMENT]

00:14:02.675 --> 00:14:04.711
And here's
our food service manager

00:14:04.711 --> 00:14:06.646
who takes good care of us
every year.

00:14:06.646 --> 00:14:08.314
Madame Catherine.

00:14:08.314 --> 00:14:10.516
My job is
to make certain you have

00:14:10.516 --> 00:14:13.386
the most delicious meals
all week long.

00:14:13.386 --> 00:14:15.621
Of course, I have three
excellent chefs to help me.

00:14:15.621 --> 00:14:17.256
The best.

00:14:17.256 --> 00:14:19.225
JESSIE/JAMES/MEOWTH
Hi ho, campers.

00:14:19.225 --> 00:14:21.361
Alright, at our camp,
we have a system

00:14:21.361 --> 00:14:23.796
where each team earns points

00:14:23.796 --> 00:14:25.565
depending on how they did
in each day's activities.

00:14:25.565 --> 00:14:27.100
Let's have fun.

00:14:27.100 --> 00:14:28.301
BONNIE/SERENA/CLEMONT
Right.

00:14:28.301 --> 00:14:30.970
Okay, Team Froakie,
let's go!

00:14:30.970 --> 00:14:34.073
Ready, Team Squirtle?
Let's do it with style.

00:14:34.073 --> 00:14:35.608
‐ Right.
‐ We'll do our best.

00:14:35.608 --> 00:14:37.710
First place gets ten points.

00:14:37.710 --> 00:14:39.512
Second place gets
seven points.

00:14:39.512 --> 00:14:41.981
Third place gets three points.

00:14:41.981 --> 00:14:44.751
And all other teams
get no points.

00:14:44.751 --> 00:14:47.653
The goal is to help each other
out while competing.

00:14:47.653 --> 00:14:50.356
The team that has earned
the most points by the last day

00:14:50.356 --> 00:14:52.625
will have the honor
of being inducted

00:14:52.625 --> 00:14:55.461
into the Pokémon summer camp
hall of fame.

00:14:55.461 --> 00:14:58.931
Also please note
the current champion Diantha

00:14:58.931 --> 00:15:01.134
was inducted into
the summer camp hall of fame

00:15:01.134 --> 00:15:03.102
back when she
was your age.

00:15:03.102 --> 00:15:05.037
‐ That's so cool.
‐ Wow!

00:15:05.037 --> 00:15:07.006
And that means
we'll be able to follow

00:15:07.006 --> 00:15:08.608
in the footsteps
of the great Diantha.

00:15:08.608 --> 00:15:11.077
I wanna do what she did.

00:15:11.077 --> 00:15:13.479
Yeah.
Pikachu, let's go for it.

00:15:13.479 --> 00:15:15.848
[AGREEMENT]

00:15:15.848 --> 00:15:18.184
Now, on our first day, we like
to get everyone acquainted

00:15:18.184 --> 00:15:20.553
by starting off
with a Pokémon battle.

00:15:20.553 --> 00:15:23.489
'It's an annual tradition
where no points are awarded'

00:15:23.489 --> 00:15:26.359
so feel free to challenge
any Trainer you like.

00:15:26.359 --> 00:15:29.896
I want my opponent to be Tierno.
We'll battle for sure this time.

00:15:29.896 --> 00:15:34.267
‐ Alright.
‐ Serena, what do you say?

00:15:34.267 --> 00:15:36.235
So that means I'll be
your opponent.

00:15:36.235 --> 00:15:38.037
And may the best Trainer win.

00:15:42.475 --> 00:15:43.009
PROFESSOR SYCAMORE
'Is everybody ready?'

00:15:45.011 --> 00:15:46.979
Battles begin.

00:15:46.979 --> 00:15:49.248
[blowing whistle]

00:15:49.248 --> 00:15:51.517
[APPEARING]

00:15:58.257 --> 00:15:59.459
Ready, Froakie?

00:15:59.459 --> 00:16:01.294
[AFFIRMATIVE]

00:16:01.294 --> 00:16:03.429
Pikachu, cheer us on
with Bonnie, alright?

00:16:03.429 --> 00:16:05.798
[EXCITED]
You can do it , Ash.

00:16:05.798 --> 00:16:08.301
You're using Froakie
not Pikachu.

00:16:08.301 --> 00:16:10.336
I got Froakie
from Professor Sycamore

00:16:10.336 --> 00:16:12.271
when I first got
to the Kalos region.

00:16:12.271 --> 00:16:15.374
Alright.
A Water‐type battle.

00:16:15.374 --> 00:16:17.610
There's no doubt we both want
to get into the hall of fame.

00:16:17.610 --> 00:16:20.313
Yep. There's no holding back.

00:16:20.313 --> 00:16:21.914
Let's win this with style.

00:16:23.182 --> 00:16:24.584
[EXCITED]

00:16:24.584 --> 00:16:27.253
Huh?
[AWE]

00:16:27.253 --> 00:16:29.388
Hey, you could be
a bit more excited.

00:16:29.388 --> 00:16:31.257
Huh?

00:16:31.257 --> 00:16:33.459
You see, this is the first time
I'm competing

00:16:33.459 --> 00:16:34.994
in an official battle
with a real judge.

00:16:34.994 --> 00:16:36.629
[AFFIRMATIVE]

00:16:36.629 --> 00:16:39.365
Huh?
Even though you're a Trainer?

00:16:39.365 --> 00:16:41.968
‐ Yeah. This is it.
‐ Amazing!

00:16:41.968 --> 00:16:44.770
That means today is your
official debut Pokémon battle.

00:16:44.770 --> 00:16:47.139
You're right.
I guess it is.

00:16:47.139 --> 00:16:48.808
Let's do our best, Fennekin.

00:16:48.808 --> 00:16:51.444
[AGREEMENT]

00:16:51.444 --> 00:16:53.012
Charmander,
let's really focus, okay?

00:16:53.012 --> 00:16:54.847
[AGREEMENT]

00:16:54.847 --> 00:16:57.250
Chespin, we've got to win this,
alright?

00:16:57.250 --> 00:16:59.318
[AGREEMENT]

00:16:59.318 --> 00:17:01.554
‐ Would you look at that.
‐ Pokémon aplenty.

00:17:01.554 --> 00:17:03.256
Yep. Stealer's choice.

00:17:03.256 --> 00:17:04.724
JESSIE/JAMES/MEOWTH
Rejoice.

00:17:04.724 --> 00:17:06.626
Excuse me,
but there's a dinner

00:17:06.626 --> 00:17:08.528
that's begging
to be prepared, right?

00:17:08.528 --> 00:17:09.562
JESSIE/JAMES/MEOWTH
Right.

00:17:09.562 --> 00:17:11.597
[EXERTION]

00:17:11.597 --> 00:17:13.466
[WATER GUN ATTACK]

00:17:13.466 --> 00:17:16.102
[EXERTION]
Fennekin, use Flamethrower!

00:17:16.102 --> 00:17:17.603
[FLAMETHROWER MOVE]

00:17:17.603 --> 00:17:18.838
Use Energy Ball.

00:17:18.838 --> 00:17:20.540
[ENERGY BALL MOVE]

00:17:22.241 --> 00:17:23.643
[SHOCK] / [EXERTION]

00:17:23.643 --> 00:17:25.711
Hey, Fennekin, are you okay?

00:17:25.711 --> 00:17:28.614
[AFFIRMATIVE]
What power.

00:17:28.614 --> 00:17:31.050
Despite it not being very
effective against Fire types.

00:17:31.050 --> 00:17:34.854
See? And cute too.
That's power with style.

00:17:34.854 --> 00:17:36.656
My dream is to one day become

00:17:36.656 --> 00:17:38.658
the world's greatest
Pokémon performer.

00:17:38.658 --> 00:17:40.326
World's greatest
Pokémon performer?

00:17:40.326 --> 00:17:41.928
[CONFUSED]

00:17:41.928 --> 00:17:43.696
Wow, you've never
heard of them?

00:17:43.696 --> 00:17:45.431
They're Trainers who create
high‐quality performances

00:17:45.431 --> 00:17:47.500
working together
with their Pokémon.

00:17:47.500 --> 00:17:48.367
Dodge it, quick!

00:17:49.835 --> 00:17:51.270
[EXERTION]

00:17:53.005 --> 00:17:56.475
[PANIC]

00:17:56.475 --> 00:18:00.179
Chespin. Calm down, please.
Come on, calm down.

00:18:00.179 --> 00:18:02.748
[RELIEVED]

00:18:02.748 --> 00:18:05.017
Please excuse us.

00:18:05.017 --> 00:18:06.419
'Chespin,
can you still battle?'

00:18:06.419 --> 00:18:08.988
[AFFIRMATIVE]

00:18:08.988 --> 00:18:11.557
[WATER PULSE ATTACK]
[EXERTION]

00:18:11.557 --> 00:18:14.393
‐ Ah. How does it do that?
‐ It's the rhythm.

00:18:14.393 --> 00:18:16.629
‐ 'The rhythm?'
‐ Word up.

00:18:16.629 --> 00:18:19.532
My dream is for my Pokémon
and I to be a Rap Dance team.

00:18:19.532 --> 00:18:22.068
‐ Sounds awesome.
‐ You bet.

00:18:22.068 --> 00:18:24.570
We're using rhythm and dance
steps while we're battling.

00:18:24.570 --> 00:18:26.105
Dodging is a breeze
when you're able to move

00:18:26.105 --> 00:18:27.640
and groove like us.

00:18:27.640 --> 00:18:29.542
Okay, Rapid Spin. Let's go.

00:18:29.542 --> 00:18:32.111
[RAPID SPIN MOVE]

00:18:32.111 --> 00:18:34.180
Froakie, Water Pulse again!

00:18:34.180 --> 00:18:35.615
[WATER PULSE MOVE]

00:18:35.615 --> 00:18:37.917
[FEAR]

00:18:37.917 --> 00:18:39.819
Alright.
This battle's over.

00:18:39.819 --> 00:18:41.354
I'm going to stop the battle.

00:18:41.354 --> 00:18:42.888
which means Squirtle
is the winner.

00:18:42.888 --> 00:18:45.958
[EXERTION]

00:18:45.958 --> 00:18:47.927
Pretty cool, huh?

00:18:47.927 --> 00:18:49.028
Looks like we'll be getting
into the hall of fame.

00:18:49.028 --> 00:18:51.464
Ah..

00:18:51.464 --> 00:18:53.432
Wow! You two can really move.

00:18:53.432 --> 00:18:55.001
[EXERTION]

00:18:57.770 --> 00:19:01.374
[AWE]

